1530	 *   for dashboard/task aggregation workloads.
1531	 *
1532	 * ⚠️  NEVER AWAIT THIS FUNCTION.
1533	 * The returned Promise resolves when both debounce timers fire. Awaiting can
1534	 * stall the HTTP response and must be avoided in request handlers.
1535	 *
1536	 * Always call as fire-and-forget:
1537	 *   refreshTaskAggregation(customerId).catch(() => {});
1538	 *
1539	 * SIGTERM behaviour: timers in _taskPerfRefreshTimers / _actionScoresRefreshTimers are lost if the process
1540	 * exits during a debounce window. This is acceptable — mv_task_action_performance
1541	 * is eventually consistent and will self-heal on the next outcome log.
1542	 * decision-writer.ts has a SIGTERM flush for decisions (which are durable);
1543	 * MV refreshes deliberately do not, since they are idempotent and cheap.
